narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Lecture on theory readings, a weekly response to the readings, and section. Trips to the Yale Center for British Art during the Media half of the course.
An exploration of our notions of media and what our interaction with media says about our way of life and of thinking. A cross between an art, philosophy and history class.
A directed survey of media writings, beginning with Walter Benjamin and making a passage through the panorama, film and eventually the electronic screen.

A theory course that is incredibly relevant to modern life, that is still evolving and wanting our contribution to the dialogue. Cassette is a passionate and endearing professor. Loved him. I wish I made use of office hour more so I could get to know him more.
